026/**
027 * A limited subset of JSON-Schema's items object.
028 *
029 * <p>
030 * It is used by parameter definitions that are not located in "body".
031 *
032 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
033 * <p class='bjava'>
034 *    <jc>// Construct using SwaggerBuilder.</jc>
035 *    Items <jv>items</jv> = <jsm>items</jsm>(<js>"string"</js>).minLength(2);
036 *
037 *    <jc>// Serialize using JsonSerializer.</jc>
038 *    String <jv>json</jv> = JsonSerializer.<jsf>DEFAULT</jsf>.toString(<jv>items</jv>);
039 *
040 *    <jc>// Or just use toString() which does the same as above.</jc>
041 *    <jv>json</jv> = <jv>items</jv>.toString();
042 * </p>
043 * <p class='bjson'>
044 *    <jc>// Output</jc>
045 *    {
046 *       <js>"type"</js>: <js>"string"</js>,
047 *       <js>"minLength"</js>: 2
048 *    }
049 * </p>
050 *
051 * <ul class='seealso'>
052 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="../../../../../overview-summary.html#juneau-rest-server.jrs.Swagger">Overview &gt; juneau-rest-server &gt; Swagger</a>
053 * </ul>
054 */
055@Bean(properties="type,format,items,collectionFormat,default,maximum,exclusiveMaximum,minimum,exclusiveMinimum,maxLength,minLength,pattern,maxItems,minItems,uniqueItems,enum,multipleOf,$ref,*")
056@FluentSetters
057public class Items extends SwaggerElement {

059   private static final String[] VALID_TYPES = {"string", "number", "integer", "boolean", "array"};

082   private Object _default;

090   /**
091    * Copy constructor.
092    *
093    * @param copyFrom The object to copy.
094    */
095   public Items(Items copyFrom) {
096      super(copyFrom);
097
098      this.collectionFormat = copyFrom.collectionFormat;
099      this._default = copyFrom._default;
100      this._enum = copyOf(copyFrom._enum);
101      this.exclusiveMaximum = copyFrom.exclusiveMaximum;
102      this.exclusiveMinimum = copyFrom.exclusiveMinimum;
103      this.format = copyFrom.format;
104      this.items = copyFrom.items == null ? null : copyFrom.items.copy();
105      this.maximum = copyFrom.maximum;
106      this.maxItems = copyFrom.maxItems;
107      this.maxLength = copyFrom.maxLength;
108      this.minimum = copyFrom.minimum;
109      this.minItems = copyFrom.minItems;
110      this.minLength = copyFrom.minLength;
111      this.multipleOf = copyFrom.multipleOf;
112      this.pattern = copyFrom.pattern;
113      this.ref = copyFrom.ref;
114      this.type = copyFrom.type;
115      this.uniqueItems = copyFrom.uniqueItems;
116   }

636   @Override /* SwaggerElement */
637   public <T> T get(String property, Class<T> type) {
638      if (property == null)
639         return null;
640      switch (property) {
641         case "collectionFormat": return toType(getCollectionFormat(), type);
642         case "default": return toType(getDefault(), type);
643         case "enum": return toType(getEnum(), type);
644         case "exclusiveMaximum": return toType(getExclusiveMaximum(), type);
645         case "exclusiveMinimum": return toType(getExclusiveMinimum(), type);
646         case "format": return toType(getFormat(), type);
647         case "items": return toType(getItems(), type);
648         case "maximum": return toType(getMaximum(), type);
649         case "maxItems": return toType(getMaxItems(), type);
650         case "maxLength": return toType(getMaxLength(), type);
651         case "minimum": return toType(getMinimum(), type);
652         case "minItems": return toType(getMinItems(), type);
653         case "minLength": return toType(getMinLength(), type);
654         case "multipleOf": return toType(getMultipleOf(), type);
655         case "pattern": return toType(getPattern(), type);
656         case "$ref": return toType(getRef(), type);
657         case "type": return toType(getType(), type);
658         case "uniqueItems": return toType(getUniqueItems(), type);
659         default: return super.get(property, type);
660      }
661   }

663   @Override /* SwaggerElement */
664   public Items set(String property, Object value) {
665      if (property == null)
666         return this;
667      switch (property) {
668         case "collectionFormat": return setCollectionFormat(stringify(value));
669         case "default": return setDefault(value);
670         case "enum": return setEnum(listBuilder(Object.class).sparse().addAny(value).build());
671         case "exclusiveMaximum": return setExclusiveMaximum(toBoolean(value));
672         case "exclusiveMinimum": return setExclusiveMinimum(toBoolean(value));
673         case "format": return setFormat(stringify(value));
674         case "items": return setItems(toType(value,Items.class));
675         case "maximum": return setMaximum(toNumber(value));
676         case "maxItems": return setMaxItems(toInteger(value));
677         case "maxLength": return setMaxLength(toInteger(value));
678         case "minimum": return setMinimum(toNumber(value));
679         case "minItems": return setMinItems(toInteger(value));
680         case "minLength": return setMinLength(toInteger(value));
681         case "multipleOf": return setMultipleOf(toNumber(value));
682         case "pattern": return setPattern(stringify(value));
683         case "$ref": return setRef(stringify(value));
684         case "type": return setType(stringify(value));
685         case "uniqueItems": return setUniqueItems(toBoolean(value));
686         default:
687            super.set(property, value);
688            return this;
689      }

717   /**
718    * Resolves any <js>"$ref"</js> attributes in this element.
719    *
720    * @param swagger The swagger document containing the definitions.
721    * @param refStack Keeps track of previously-visited references so that we don't cause recursive loops.
722    * @param maxDepth
723    *    The maximum depth to resolve references.
724    *    <br>After that level is reached, <c>$ref</c> references will be left alone.
725    *    <br>Useful if you have very complex models and you don't want your swagger page to be overly-complex.
726    * @return
727    *    This object with references resolved.
728    *    <br>May or may not be the same object.
729    */
730   public Items resolveRefs(Swagger swagger, Deque<String> refStack, int maxDepth) {
731
732      if (ref != null) {
733         if (refStack.contains(ref) || refStack.size() >= maxDepth)
734            return this;
735         refStack.addLast(ref);
736         Items r = swagger.findRef(ref, Items.class).resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
737         refStack.removeLast();
738         return r;
739      }
740
741      set("properties", resolveRefs(get("properties"), swagger, refStack, maxDepth));
742
743      if (items != null)
744         items = items.resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
745
746      set("example", null);
747
748      return this;
749   }
750
751   /* Resolve references in extra attributes */
752   private Object resolveRefs(Object o, Swagger swagger, Deque<String> refStack, int maxDepth) {
753      if (o instanceof JsonMap) {
754         JsonMap om = (JsonMap)o;
755         Object ref = om.get("$ref");
756         if (ref instanceof CharSequence) {
757            String sref = ref.toString();
758            if (refStack.contains(sref) || refStack.size() >= maxDepth)
759               return o;
760            refStack.addLast(sref);
761            Object o2 = swagger.findRef(sref, Object.class);
762            o2 = resolveRefs(o2, swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
763            refStack.removeLast();
764            return o2;
765         }
766         om.entrySet().forEach(x -> x.setValue(resolveRefs(x.getValue(), swagger, refStack, maxDepth)));
767      }
768      if (o instanceof JsonList)
769         for (ListIterator<Object> li = ((JsonList)o).listIterator(); li.hasNext();)
770            li.set(resolveRefs(li.next(), swagger, refStack, maxDepth));
771      return o;
772   }
773}
